explanation: This solution iterates through the input string, checking if the current substring is "abc". If it is, it moves the pointer 3 positions ahead. If not, it calculates the minimum number of characters needed to make the remaining substring "abc" and adds it to the result. This approach has a high efficiency due to its simplicity and the fact that it only needs to iterate through the input string once.

